;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-101_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-102_ pf-text-1"><strong>Ensuring patient safety</strong> - CQC-regulated organisations play a pivotal role in safeguarding the safety and well-being of patients and service users. By adhering to stringent regulatory standards, these organisations mitigate risks and prevent harm, fostering trust and confidence among service users.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-104_ pf-text-1"><strong>Promoting quality of care</strong> - Effective CQC-regulated organisations are committed to delivering high-quality care that meets the diverse needs of patients and service users. Through continuous quality improvement initiatives and adherence to best practices, these organisations strive to achieve positive outcomes and enhance the overall experience of care recipients.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-106_ pf-text-1"><strong>Enhancing accountability and transparency</strong> - The CQC regulates healthcare and social care settings to promote accountability and transparency. By subjecting providers to rigorous inspections and assessments, the CQC holds them accountable for their performance and encourages openness in reporting and addressing areas for improvement.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-108_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mastering_CQC_Compliance_ComplyPlus_Healthcare_Governance_Solutions_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1711616702" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mastering_CQC_Compliance_ComplyPlus_Healthcare_Governance_Solutions_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1711616702 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mastering_CQC_Compliance_ComplyPlus_Healthcare_Governance_Solutions_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_10